@{
    ViewData["Title"] = " Articles ";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <style>
        .card {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            height: 80%;
        }
        .card-body {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: space-between;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container mt-5">
        <h2 class="mb-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h2>
        <div class="row">
            <!-- Card 1 -->
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Creating a Like Button that Increments When Clicked</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
                            Learn how to implement a like button in your web application that dynamically updates the like count every time it's clicked. This tutorial covers JavaScript and backend integration. 
                            <a href="https://medium.com/zablon.nyabuto/creating-a-like-button-that-increments-when-clicked-50d841a189c9" target="_blank">Read more</a>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Card 2 -->
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Understanding MVC Architecture in .NET</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
                            An overview of the Model-View-Controller (MVC) architecture pattern, its benefits in .NET development, and how to effectively structure your projects for maintainability and scalability.
                            <a href="https://medium.com/zablon.nyabuto/understanding-mvc-architecture-in-net-f08a71725547" target="_blank">Read more</a>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Card 3 -->
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Tips for Optimizing SQL Queries in .NET</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
                            Improve the performance of your .NET applications by learning advanced SQL optimization techniques. This guide covers indexing, query tuning, and best practices for database interaction.
                            <a href="https://medium.com/zablon.nyabuto/tips-for-optimizing-sql-queries-in-net-56f2933cd82e" target="_blank">Read more</a>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Card 4 -->
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Secure Coding Practices in Web Development</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
                            Explore the essential practices for writing secure code in web development. This article delves into authentication, authorization, data validation, and how to protect against common vulnerabilities.
                            <a href="https://medium.com/zablon.nyabuto/secure-coding-practices-in-web-development-466775be58ab" target="_blank">Read more</a>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.5.1.slim.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/popperjs/core@2.5.3/dist/umd/popper.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>

